{"type":"message","id":"be3e931d","parentId":"f397d9d8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T20:08:35.332Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pfg3y8cmkcrv_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 160141\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: an (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best single action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- Recent work on CFI Compression showed that binary CFI thresholds fail due to \"constant format\" tokens\r\n- Key insight: Need a hybrid formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n- Next action is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment\r\n\r\nThe pending action is clearly the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C). This is the logical next step that follows from the insights gained in the CFI compression experiment.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Write an updated pulse script that implements the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Run the experiment on 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the new results\r\n\r\nLet me write the action to implement and run this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI compression synthesis identified that binary thresholds fail due to constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1), and proposed a hybrid formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This experiment needs to be run to validate the approach.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nImplement the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment in a new PowerShell script, run it against the 200-pulse corpus, and update the synthesis document with results.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n# Strategy C: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n# Hypothesis: Distinguishes constant-format (freq~160, CFI=1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$SampleSize = 200,\r\n    [float]$TrainSplit = 0.8\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$RootDir = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir\r\n\r\n# Load pulse data\r\n$PulseDir = \"$RootDir\\state\\pulses\"\r\n$Pulses = Get-ChildItem \"$PulseDir\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name | Select-Object -First $SampleSize\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment ===\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Sample: $($Pulses.Count) pulses\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Token frequency counting\r\n$GlobalFreq = @{}\r\n$PerPulseFreq = @()\r\n\r\nforeach ($pulse in $Pulses) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    $tokenCounts = @{}\r\n    foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n        $tokenCounts[$t] = ++$GlobalFreq[$t]\r\n    }\r\n    $PerPulseFreq += $tokenCounts\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Calculate CFI for each token\r\n$TokenStats = @{}\r\n$TotalPulses = $Pulses.Count\r\n\r\nforeach ($token in $GlobalFreq.Keys) {\r\n    $freq = $GlobalFreq[$token]\r\n    $cfi = $freq / $TotalPulses\r\n    \r\n    # Hybrid score: CFI × min(1, freq/120)\r\n    # For freq=160: score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (max, but freq>120 so clamped)\r\n    # For freq=120: score = 0.75 × 1.0 = 0.75\r\n    # For freq=60: score = 0.375 × 0.5 = 0.1875\r\n    # For freq=3: score = 0.015 × 0.025 = 0.000375\r\n    $hybridScore = $cfi * [Math]::Min(1, $freq / 120)\r\n    \r\n    $TokenStats[$token] = @{\r\n        freq = $freq\r\n        cfi = $cfi\r\n        hybridScore = $hybridScore\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Split into train/test\r\n$TrainCount = [Math]::Floor($Pulses.Count * $TrainSplit)\r\n$TrainPulses = $Pulses[0..($TrainCount-1)]\r\n$TestPulses = $Pulses[$TrainCount..($Pulses.Count-1)]\r\n\r\n# Train: find optimal hybrid threshold\r\n$TrainFreq = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $TrainPulses) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $pulse.FullName -Raw\r\n    $tokens = [regex]::Matches($content, '\\S+') | ForEach-Object { $_.Value }\r\n    foreach ($t in $tokens) {\r\n        $TrainFreq[$t] = ++$TrainFreq[$t]\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Find threshold that maximizes precision on research tokens\r\n# \"Research tokens\" = tokens with freq >= 3 (appear multiple times meaningfully)\r\n$ResearchTokens = $TrainFreq.Keys | Where-Object { $TrainFreq[$_] -ge 3 }\r\n$NonResearchTokens = $TrainFreq.Keys | Where-Object { $TrainFreq[$_] -lt 3 }\r\n\r\n$BestThreshold = 0\r\n$BestF1 = 0\r\n\r\nforeach ($threshold in @(0.01, 0.02, 0.05, 0.1, 0.15, 0.2, 0.25, 0.3)) {\r\n    $TruePositives = 0\r\n    $FalsePositives = 0\r\n    $TrueNegatives = 0\r\n   \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 0\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 16:02:04\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774382915330}}
